# Passing Props Down the Tree

In React, data flows down from parent to child via props. This works well for shallow component trees. But when many components need the same data, you end up passing it through intermediate components that don't use it themselves – just to get it deeper.

This is called **prop drilling**.

Example:
```jsx
function App() {
  const [user, setUser] = useState(null);
  return <Header user={user} />;
}

function Header({ user }) {
  return <Avatar user={user} />; // Header doesn't need user, just passes it
}

function Avatar({ user }) {
  return <Image source={{ uri: user.avatar }} />;
}
```
